<h2>Head coach departs after defeat by West Ham leaves club three points off relegation zone</h2><br><br>
Watford have announced the departure of head coach Nigel Pearson.<p>
His exit comes after Watford’s 3-1 defeat by West Ham United on Friday left the Hornets 
only three points clear of the relegation zone with two matches remaining,<p>
at home to Manchester City and away to Arsenal.<p>
Pearson was appointed head coach in December 2019, succeeding Quique Sanchez Flores.<p>
It is the club’s third managerial change of the season after Sanchez Flores had replaced Javi Gracia in September last year.<p>
The club have announced that former player Hayden Mullins, assisted by Graham Stack, will be in charge of the final two matches.<br><br>
